🌗 Light & Dark Mode
Added a theme toggle button (bottom-right corner of every page) to switch between light and dark mode
Your preference is remembered across pages and sessions
Service and government pages default to light mode; all other pages default to dark mode
Dark mode now properly styles every element: cards, forms, navigation, footer, sidebars, icons, and backgrounds
📱 Mobile Homepage (mobile.html)
Tapping the theme toggle now actually changes the look of the page (was broken before — the page stayed dark regardless)
Service cards in "Quick Access" now have a red top border, matching the desktop style
Quick Access and News sections now scroll horizontally instead of stacking vertically
Each Quick Access card now shows a custom icon (ID card, tax, health, etc.) instead of generic shapes
Service descriptions are now capped to one line so cards stay compact
📱 Mobile — All Pages
Service grids, news grids, ministry lists, and branch cards now scroll horizontally on mobile instead of showing tiny squished columns
Service action cards on subpages (e.g. "National Identity Card", "Passport") now also scroll horizontally
Category header sections (icon + title + description) now stack vertically on mobile instead of being crushed side by side
Large desktop padding on sections is automatically reduced on mobile
🐛 Bug Fixes
Fixed a 404 error when clicking "Government" in the main navigation
Fixed the site logo (emblem) being invisible in certain theme/background combinations
Fixed the browser tab icon conflicting with the in-page logo — they are now separate files
Fixed hamburger menu bars being invisible on dark-themed pages
Fixed footer text being invisible in light mode (footer is now always dark)
Fixed the active navigation link showing black text on a black background
Fixed the "Need Help?" sidebar card staying dark when switching to light mode
🧹 Code Cleanup
Removed duplicate and redundant CSS rules across all shared stylesheets
Consolidated repeated code patterns into reusable blocks
Added .gitignore to keep internal tooling files out of the repository
